                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JOSIAH WESTLEY</hi>.")</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18511027-name-293" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-293" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-293" type="surname" value="M'CABE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-293" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN M'CABE</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at York, and am assistant to Mr. Sunter, a book-seller. I have been engaged in the book trade at York twelve years—I never heard of a bookseller named Gilbert in York—I have a knowledge of all booksellers in York—I know a Mr. Gilbert, of Sheffield, who occasionally comes to York to transact business—there are from twenty to thirty book-sellers in York.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18511027-name-294" type="witnessName">
